news.title: Awfis posts net profit of 11.23 crore in Q4 FY25, elevates Sumit Lakhani as CEO
news.para: Awfis Space Solutions' net consolidated total income stood at ₹359.45 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 49.09 per cent from ₹241.10 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Kolte-Patil Developers reports net profit of ₹66.29 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: Kolte-Patil Developers' net consolidated total income stood at ₹723.20 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 37.04 per cent from ₹527.71 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year.

news.title: Illegal sand mining alters Yamuna’s course in Sonipat: Irrigation department report
news.para: In a report submitted after a field inspection on May 22, a four-member team of the department led by R K Bodwal, superintending engineer (SE), Sonipat, has flagged widespread illegal mining activity.

news.title: Kolkata: NDITA to conduct fire audit at 250 sector V buildings soon
news.para: Officials said fire audits of most of the buildings within NDITA are conducted at regular intervals. But the authorities have decided to step up inspections following recent fire hazards in some buildings in and around the city and several establishments found violating fire safety norms..

news.title: Goa housing board to collaborate with private players to provide affordable homes
news.para: GHB chairman Jit Arolkar said the decision was taken to generate revenue for the board and purchase new properties to provide affordable housing to residents of Goa.

news.title: Flat sale agreement not must for relief under real estate law: MREAT
news.para: Allottee Stanley Saldanha, who was represented by advocate Anil D' Souza, had booked a flat in Aug 2013 in an IndiaBulls project at Panvel and had paid a sum of over Rs 26 lakh.

news.title: Mumbai: Court tells Pali Hill society to vacate land leased from Kamal Amrohi & Meena Kumari in 1959
news.para: In 1959, legendary actor Meena Kumari and her husband, film director Kamal Amrohi, jointly purchased a 2.5-acre Pali Hill plot for a reported Rs 5 lakh and leased it to a developer, who constructed five buildings named Cozihom Cooperative Housing Society.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines builder for failing to register Aura Velimala Phase 1
news.para: Additionally, the authority directed the builder to refund amounts paid by 62 allottees along with 11% interest. The complainants, M Prem Kumar of Dilsukhnagar and others, stated they entered into unregistered agreements of sale with the respondents, with possession promised by Dec 2023.

news.title: Jaiprakash Associates' lenders approve ₹936 crore cash outflow for Q1 FY26
news.para: According to a regulatory filing on Saturday, Jaiprakash Associates informed that a Committee of Creditors (COC) has approved "the budgeted cash outflows of the Corporate Debtor for the period from April 01, 2025, to June 30, 2025, of up to INR 936.27 crores".

news.title: Panels set up for fire safety audit, norm compliance across West Bengal
news.para: The committees were set up by state chief secretary Manoj Pant on Thursday following the recent spate of fires in the city and other parts of the state, resulting in the loss of lives and property.

news.title: Pune civic body issues evacuation notice to residents of Padmavatinagar Society building
news.para: " If you fail to do so, we will be compelled to exercise our rights under Section 268 (7) of the Maharashtra Municipal Corporation Act, and if necessary, with the assistance of the police, to vacate the premises you are occupying," the PMC notice read.

news.title: Prayagraj administration cracks down on 2,000 PMAY defaulters
news.para: After sending notices, the administration is now preparing to issue Recovery Certificates (RCs) from the respective tehsils to reclaim the misused public funds.

news.title: Over 70,000 housing societies in Maharashtra can now apply online for deemed conveyance
news.para: The new system eliminates the need for multiple visits to deputy registrar's office, allowing over 70,000 eligible societies to complete the entire process — from submission to certification — of procuring deemed conveyance digitally, said a senior official of the state cooperation department.

news.title: Oyo owned Belvilla acquires short-term rental platform MadeComfy
news.para: As part of the deal, the company will issue shares worth $ 1.9 million (Rs 16 crore) upfront at $ 0.67 (Rs 57.09) a piece - valuing Belvilla's parent entity Oyo at close to $ 5 billion (Rs 42,500 crore) and deferred stocks post two years worth $ 9.6 million (Rs 81 crore).

news.title: JK Cement's profit jumps 64.4% to ₹361.3 crore in Q4 FY25
news.para: JK Cement's revenue from operations was up 15.3 per cent at Rs 3,581.18 crore in the March quarter. It was at Rs 3,105.77 crore in the corresponding period a year ago.

news.title: PAC issues legal notice to authorities over illegal constructions on green areas in Ludhiana
news.para: The Public Action Committee (PAC)  served the notice to the principal secretary of the local bodies department, the municipal corporation of Ludhiana, and LIT, warning of legal action in NGT if construction on protected green spaces is not halted and reversed within three weeks.

news.title: Analjit Singh transfers Lutyens’ Delhi bungalow to Vstar Ventures in ₹152 crore internal deal
news.para: Sahil Vachani—Vice Chairman and Managing Director of Max Estates, and Singh’s son-in-law—represented Vstar Ventures in the deal.

news.title: Mohali development body pulls down 30 illegal structures in Jhampur, sector 39
news.para: The demolition drive, led by Gmada officer Arvind Pannu, began at 11.30 am and continued till 4 pm. About 25 houses under construction and other illegal structures were razed in Jhampur village alone.

news.title: About 50 builders show interest in Mumbai civic body's slum rehabilitation plan
news.para: These included Adani Realty, Wadhwa Group, Rustomjee, Dosti Realty, JSW Realty, DHS Group, Jalaram Developers, Nilyog Developers, Asha Developers, and Chandak Realty, among others.

news.title: Delhi: MCD makes registration on DPCC dust portal mandatory for building plan approval
news.para: The MCD has also been asked to ensure that these environmental safeguards are built into the very process of sanctioning building plans and that violations result in denial or cancellation of project permissions.
